keColor=#b85450;fontSize=10;" edge="1" parent="1" source="8466_4" target="8466_23"><mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="8466_25" value="APPROACHES per stage —  Base functionality: dry-run / --quick smoke, no API (A6 · A8).   Meets spec: schema validation + Run-Contract conformance (R3 · G1 · G2).   Challenge: Option A meta-eval + Option B independence controls + Option C ensemble.   Independence (A2 · D1): attacker ≠ judge ≠ target model families · neutral re-judge · multi-seed + mutator ablation (avoids co-adaptation confound).   Every gate deterministic (A1 · R9); nothing bypasses the adapter (R2). This pipeline is workflow W-C." style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#ffffff;strokeColor=#cccccc;dashed=1;fontSize=10;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontColor=#555555;spacingLeft=8;spacingTop=6;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="40" y="500" width="1560" height="130" as="geometry"/></mxCell></root></mxGraphModel></diagram><diagram name="Frontier Vendor Integration Map" id="Frontier_Vendor_Integration_Map"><mxGraphModel dx="1420" dy="900" grid="1" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" page="1" pageScale="1" pageWidth="1600" pageHeight="1160" math="0" shadow="0"><root><mxCell id="0"/><mxCell id="1" parent="0"/><mxCell id="5239_1" value="Frontier Vendor Integration Map — where each plugs in (lane · layer · harnesses)" style="text;html=1;fontSize=20;fontStyle=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="40" y="18" width="1200" height="30" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="5239_2" value="Modes: DRIVER (behind Run Contract) · DETECTOR (floors judge) · GUARDRAIL (inline + test target) · PLATFORM (orchestrate-above) · SUBSTRATE (glue)" style="text;html=1;fontSize=12;align=left;fontColor=#555555;verticalAlign=middle;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="40" y="48" width="1300" height="20" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="5239_3" value="ANTHROPIC — Petri / Bloom (DRIVER · autonomous alignment &amp; behavioral auditing) · Claude Agent SDK + MCP (SUBSTRATE)   →   Data plane · H1.3, agentic, H2.4   ·   aligned ✓" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#e1d5e7;strokeColor=#9673a6;fontSize=11;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="40" y="110" width="1520" height="70" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="5239_4" value="NVIDIA — Garak (DRIVER · vuln scanner, 50+ probes, Agent-breaker/GOAT) · NeMo Guardrails (GUARDRAIL + resilience test-target) · Aegis (safety model)   →   Data plane / inline · H1.2, H2.1, H2.3, H4.1   ·   aligned ✓" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#d5e8d4;strokeColor=#82b366;fontSize=11;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="40" y="190" width="1520" height="70" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="5239_5" value="MICROSOFT — PyRIT (DRIVER · orchestration: Crescendo, encoding, agentic ASR) · Azure Foundry RT Agent (CLOUD BACKEND) · Content Safety / Prompt Shields (GUARDRAIL) · Presidio (DETECTOR · PII/CPNI floor)   →   Data plane / inline · H2.1, H1.2, H2.2, H2.3   ·   aligned ✓" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#dae8fc;strokeColor=#6c8ebf;fontSize=11;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="40" y="270" width="1520" height="80" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="5239_6" value="CISCO — AI Defense (PLATFORM)  →  ORCHESTRATE-ABOVE (decided): consumed BEHIND the Run Contract as driver + OWASP·NIST·MITRE control-map (H5.3) + continuous validation.  Our deterministic gate stays authoritative.  ✓" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#e1d5e7;strokeColor=#9673a6;fontSize=11;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="40" y="360" width="1520" height="80" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="5239_7" value="OURS (glue) — LiteLLM (adapter · single I/O path · ≠ AT&amp;T Model Router) · Inspect AI (scoring substrate) · Glasswing MAP-Elites (DRIVER · QD coverage) · H1.5 Bias &amp; Fairness (Phase-1) · deterministic Gate + Judge Quorum + Detectors" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#f5f5f5;strokeColor=#999999;fontSize=12;fontStyle=1;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="40" y="450" width="1520" height="80" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="5239_8" value="Integration rules —  All DRIVERS (incl. Cisco, orchestrate-above) plug behind the Run Contract (R3) and are compared by the W-C bake-off (Page 2).  GUARDRAILS are inline (§6.17) AND tested by the Resilience harness (H4.1) — a guardrail pass is not a harness verdict.  The AT&amp;T Model Router is AT&amp;T-owned; our adapter is a separate harness-I/O path.  Provider- &amp; model-independence (R2 · A2 · D1) preserved: nothing bypasses the adapter; attacker ≠ judge ≠ target families." style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#ffffff;strokeColor=#cccccc;dashed=1;fontSize=10;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontColor=#555555;spacingLeft=8;spacingTop=6;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="40" y="548" width="1520" height="120" as="geometry"/></mxCell></root></mxGraphModel></diagram><diagram name="Use Cases by Segment" id="Use_Cases_by_Segment"><mxGraphModel dx="1420" dy="900" grid="1" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" page="1" pageScale="1" pageWidth="1600" pageHeight="900" math="0" shadow="0"><root><mxCell id="0"/><mxCell id="1" parent="0"/><mxCell id="7933_1" value="" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#1f3b73;strokeColor=none;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="0" y="0" width="1600" height="84" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="7933_2" value="Enterprise AI Harness Platform — Use Cases by Segment" style="text;html=1;fontSize=24;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#ffffff;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="32" y="18" width="1300" height="30" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="7933_3" value="What each segment is FOR · forward-deployed at AT&amp;T · provider-independent · deterministic gate" style="text;html=1;fontSize=13;fontColor=#cfe0f5;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="32" y="52" width="1400" height="20" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="7933_4" value="&lt;b&gt;1 · Sources &amp; Access&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;i&gt;For:&lt;/i&gt; onboard any model/agent — vendor-neutral.&lt;br&gt;• Onboard Hosted LLM · Databricks · Claude · Bedrock · OSS&lt;br&gt;• &quot;Swapped providers — did anything regress?&quot; (1-line config)&lt;br&gt;• Test any model behind one adapter — no rewrite (R2/A2)" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacingLeft=12;spacingTop=10;spacingRight=10;fontSize=12;fillColor=#eeeeee;strokeColor=#666666;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="32" y="100" width="366" height="340" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="7933_5" value="&lt;b&gt;2 · Discover &amp; Secure&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;i&gt;For:&lt;/i&gt; know what AI exists; block unsafe before it runs.&lt;br&gt;• Inventory assets + owners; version &amp; lineage (blast-radius)&lt;br&gt;• Block secrets · malicious model files · unapproved providers&lt;br&gt;• &quot;Safe to move downstream&quot; gate — SBOM · license · policy (W-B)" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacingLeft=12;spacingTop=10;spacingRight=10;fontSize=12;fillColor=#dae8fc;strokeColor=#6c8ebf;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="418" y="100" width="366" height="340" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="7933_6" value="&lt;b&gt;3 · Contextualize&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;i&gt;For:&lt;/i&gt; turn a business use case into required assurance.&lt;br&gt;• PII/CPNI + write-tools → auto high-risk → required harnesses&lt;br&gt;• Map to AT&amp;T Golden Controls · ISO 42001 · EU AI Act&lt;br&gt;• Deterministic, auditable &quot;what must we test&quot; (W1)" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacingLeft=12;spacingTop=10;spacingRight=10;fontSize=12;fillColor=#dae8fc;strokeColor=#6c8ebf;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="804" y="100" width="366" height="340" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="7933_7" value="&lt;b&gt;4 · Harness Execution — 5 categories&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;i&gt;For:&lt;/i&gt; measure model &amp; agent behavior (the core).&lt;br&gt;• Test: &quot;still safe?&quot; · &quot;Model A vs B?&quot; · over-refusal&lt;br&gt;• Exposure: jailbreak · injection · tool-abuse · PII/CPNI leak · cyber&lt;br&gt;• Remediation · Resilience · Governance: fix · fail-safe · coverage" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacingLeft=12;spacingTop=10;spacingRight=10;fontSize=12;fillColor=#d5e8d4;strokeColor=#82b366;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="1190" y="100" width="366" height="340" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="7933_8" value="&lt;b&gt;5 · Judge &amp; Evidence&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;i&gt;For:&lt;/i&gt; verdicts you can trust and prove.&lt;br&gt;• Multi-judge quorum + deterministic detectors (not one LLM)&lt;br&gt;• &quot;Compliance wants OWASP-LLM evidence&quot; → audit-grade, replayable&lt;br&gt;• Calibrate the evaluator itself (judge precision/recall)" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacingLeft=12;spacingTop=10;spacingRight=10;fontSize=12;fillColor=#d5e8d4;strokeColor=#82b366;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="32" y="460" width="366" height="340" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="7933_9" value="&lt;b&gt;6 · Gate &amp; Remediate&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;i&gt;For:&lt;/i&gt; stop unsafe AI before production; drive fixes.&lt;br&gt;• Block unsafe AI in CI/CD — approve/warn/block/manual_review&lt;br&gt;• PR annotations · pipeline gate · policy-versioned rationale&lt;br&gt;• Owner remediation + human-approved rollback + retest (A10)" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacingLeft=12;spacingTop=10;spacingRight=10;fontSize=12;fillColor=#ffe6cc;strokeColor=#d79b00;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="418" y="460" width="366" height="340" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="7933_10" value="&lt;b&gt;7 · Frontier Integration&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;i&gt;For:&lt;/i&gt; best-of-each red-team, no lock-in.&lt;br&gt;• PyRIT · Garak · Petri behind one Run Contract; bake-off (W-C)&lt;br&gt;• Orchestrate-above Cisco AI Defense (200+ cat · control-map)&lt;br&gt;• &quot;We need our own domain attacks&quot; → add via same contract" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacingLeft=12;spacingTop=10;spacingRight=10;fontSize=12;fillColor=#e1d5e7;strokeColor=#9673a6;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="804" y="460" width="366" height="340" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="7933_11" value="&lt;b&gt;8 · Govern &amp; Evolve&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;i&gt;For:&lt;/i&gt; continuous, auditable assurance.&lt;br&gt;• Chain-of-custody discovery → gate for auditors/regulators&lt;br&gt;• RBAC + HITL for sensitive actions (waiver · gate override)&lt;br&gt;• Evolve: drift/threat updates → re-challenge new versions" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacingLeft=12;spacingTop=10;spacingRight=10;fontSize=12;fillColor=#dae8fc;strokeColor=#6c8ebf;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="1190" y="460" width="366" height="340" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="7933_12" value="DISCOVER → SECURE → CONTEXTUALIZE → TEST → JUDGE → GATE → REMEDIATE → EVOLVE        provider-independent · deterministic gate · audit-grade evidence · forward-deployed" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#1f3b73;strokeColor=none;fontColor=#ffffff;fontSize=13;fontStyle=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="0" y="812" width="1600" height="58" as="geometry"/></mxCell></root></mxGraphModel></diagram></mxfile>